frameDefinitions: An Agent manipulates a Fastener to open or close a Containing_object (e.g. coat, jar).
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
A Cause triggers a System to operate in accordance with its intended purpose.
A Device or machine is put in (or out of) service either by a volitional Agent or by a Cause event or force acting on the Device.
An Agent initiates the beginning of an ongoing Activity in which he will be continuously involved. '' 'At the same time, city-states began to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.'
This frame describes either the creation of a Flame by a Kindler or non-sentient Cause, or the igniting of Flammables by a Kindler or a Cause.
frameExamples: Mary <t>closed</t> her coat with a belt.
Smoking a cigarette will normally not <t>set off</t> a smoke alarm.
The laborer realized that he <t>activated</t> the machine but did not know how to stop it.
At the same time, city-states <t>began</t> to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.
Taliban militants recently <t>set fire</t> to several schools.
listRoleDefinitions:
This role identifies the item that is closed by the agent with the fastener.
<fex name='Agent'>Lee</fex> <t>buttoned</t> <fex name='Containing_object'>his coat</fex>.
The Agent opens/closes the Containing-object.
This role identifies the fastener that the agent manipulates.
This role identifies the active zone of the container that may be expressed as the direct object of the target verb.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> closes the <fen>Container_portal</fen> or the <fen>Containing_object</fen>.
The location where the closing event takes place.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.
The <fen>Cause</fen> interacts with the <fen>System</fen> such that conditions are met for the <fen>System</fen> to operate.
The <fen>System</fen> interacts with or detects the <fen>Cause</fen> and activates.
An entity which participates in a <fen>Cause</fen>, perhaps volitionally and perhaps not.
The time when the triggering takes place.
Where the triggering takes place.
The <fen>Device</fen> or machine that is in or out of operation.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who changes the operational state of the <fen>Device</fen>.
<fen>Cause</fen> identifies the non-agentive force that causes the <fen>Device</fen> to begin to operate.
The <fen>Time</fen> when a <fen>Device</fen> is put into or out of operation.
The <fen>Place</fen> in which the <fen>Device</fen> is put into or out of operation.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> starts.
This role identifies the being that starts the intentional <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The <fen>Kindler</fen> is the person performing the intentional act.
The <fen>Flame</fen> is what is created by the Kindler.
The Flamables is the the object that is set on fire by the Kindler.
The cause of the fire.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>Harry</fex> uncorked the champagne.
Marcus tied his shoe <fex>with the neon-green shoelaces</fex>.
We zipped <fex>the tent flap</fex>.
They close the bank vault <fex>at precisely 5:35PM</fex>.
Shouldn't you have buttoned that <fex>in the bathroom</fex>?
He gave me another lame <fex>excuse</fex>.
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
<fex>His presence</fex> set off the motion alarms.
They let him through even though something triggered <fex>the metal detector</fex>?
<fex>She</fex> set off the silent alarm before being shoved into the middle of the lobby.
Three bombs were set off <fex>at three o'clock today</fex>.
Police came running downstairs when someone set off the metal detector <fex>at the county courthouse</fex>.
<fex>The night lights</fex> were turned on in the secondary school.
Instantly <fex>Sue</fex> activated the commlink on the wall.
He was in his stocking feet while standing in the bayou that formed when <fex>the wind</fex> turned the shower on in that one upstairs bathroom.
My dad turned the lights on for me <fex>at 10 o'clock</fex>
Suddenly, the lights got turned on <fex>on the Jamaica road bridge</fex>.
<fex>Mark</fex> started the fire with a magnifying glass.
Oscar started <fex>the fire</fex>.
Tracy set <fex>the couch</fex> on fire.
<fex>A spark</fex> ignited the curtains.
